In England, in the seven days to 10 November, there were 199,359 new confirmed cases (352.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 November, there were 219,373 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 9% (20,014 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 15 November is 8,144,766 (14,402.7 cases per 100,000 population).
